{"ts":"2026-07-19T14:43:37.560Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-xm7c"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"CLI+MCP surface for atomic bulk item mutations: JSON mutation batch on stdin over commitItemMutations"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":""},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Feature"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["cli","multi-agent","sdk-first"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-19T14:43:37.560Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T14:43:37.560Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":240},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"CLI command consumes a JSON array of {op:create|update|close} mutations on stdin and applies them atomically via the public SDK commitItemMutations only (no private-core imports); partial failure compensates per the SDK policy and reports per-mutation outcomes; --dry-run previews the batch; unknown ops/keys fail fast with contract-derived hints; idempotent resume via a stable --transaction-id; MCP parity tool + contracts/completions/docs/vitest wiring per the new-command checklist; command naming decided under the pm-pbyu noun-verb composition input before implementation"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-usfg"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"medium"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":75},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-g5sx","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-19T14:43:37.560Z"},{"id":"pm-khdq","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-19T14:43:37.560Z"},{"id":"pm-kipd","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-19T14:43:37.560Z"},{"id":"pm-pibw","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-19T14:43:37.560Z"},{"id":"pm-y9hq","kind":"discovered_from","created_at":"2026-07-19T14:43:37.560Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"ef1da288682f937c8ab67eb9ff7fa1c0d0330e0c14befd15cb8cc7727b25623a","message":"PR#616 shipped commitItemMutations (pm-y9hq) as SDK-only. Scripting agents (terminal+jq composition) and multi-agent lanes still cannot perform atomic multi-item mutations without writing TypeScript — update-many/close-many are non-transactional and pm-kipd covers only single-item stdin documents. This exposes the shipped primitive at the CLI/MCP boundary, the reverse direction of the usfg thin-layer thesis."}
